<div id="c1">
<p>I think this Shangri-La thing is pretty interesting, and I&#8217;ve tried some vegetable oil a couple hours before I run to see if it will work as &#8220;blood sugar insurance.&#8221; It&#8217;s only been a few trials, and my blood sugar crashes are sort of unpredictable, but I think it might be helping.  It&#8217;s often hard for me to time meals such that they leave me in a good state for running, so if the set point trick can make my body less susceptible to food ups and downs, I&#8217;ll be very interested.</p>

<p>I can&#8217;t help but wonder if your &#8220;supertaster&#8221; status ups the ante for the tastelessness of the oil. Do you have to get extra, extra, extra light olive oil? :)</p>

