<p>The analogy is flawed in that wealth can easily be transfered from those who have it to those who don&#8217;t, while weight itself cannot be so easily transfered (weight - not food).</p>

<p>Moreover, in the affluent West, weight-loss is <em>high-status</em> activity, which attracts much marketing, while poverty relief is the opposite, downright stigmatized these days in the US.</p>

<p>You really should entertain the idea that you&#8217;re mistaken, and that people who have seen lots of fads come and go are correct.</p>

