<div id="c7">
<p>There&#8217;s a difference between &#8216;why don&#8217;t you just work your way out of poverty&#8217; and &#8216;why don&#8217;t you just starve your way out of obesity&#8217;. Unless you are obese due to some disease, you <em>can</em> work your way out of obesity if you really decide to do so and can keep to that decision. Yes, I know that the latter part can be difficult, especially if you live a stressed life. But &#8220;working your way out of poverty&#8221; isn&#8217;t up to you just deciding to do so and sticking to it. Even most &#8220;rich&#8221; people as individuals have very little control over the economy, let alone poor people. But you can have full control over what enters your gastrointestinal tract.</p>

