<div id="c14">
<p>While I agree with the &#8220;backlash&#8221; (a notoriously loaded term, BTW), I take issue with tuomov&#8217;s &#8220;no pain, no loss&#8221; motto. It seems long-term success often involves learning to derive great satisfaction from what at first glance involves sacrifice. If you&#8217;ve been eating moderately and exercising routinely for a while now and still regard it negatively as &#8220;starvation and strenuous exercise,&#8221; you&#8217;re not getting it, and need a major reorientation.</p>

<p class="posted">posted by Mike Sierra
